  "body": "I just ran into the following issue: Using a linear gradient as a background image for an element and dynamically updating this gradient does not seem to work in Firefox (I'm running v28.0) as the style attribute of the DOM node does not get updated. It works fine in Chromium though.\n\nHere is a code snippet:\n\n``` javascript\nvar Hello = React.createClass({\n    render: function() {\n        var value = this.props.value;\n        var gradient = 'linear-gradient(to right, #141414 '+value+'%, #777777 '+value+'%)';\n        var style = { 'background-image': gradient };\n        return <div style={style}>{this.props.value}</div>;\n    }\n});\n```\n\nYou can play around with a working example over here: http://jsfiddle.net/kb3gN/1634/\n",
